column4: having a problem install my deb package, can anyone help me out?
having a problem install my deb package, can anyone help me out?
having a problem install my deb package, can anyone help me out?
What seems to be the problem?
Errors were encountered while processing: openvpn
did you got my msg
Yes.  You'd be wise to settle down a bit though.  Helping takes time.  What command did you run?
sudo dpkg -i openvpn_2.2-beta5-ubuntu0_i386.deb
Use a paste site (e.g. http://goo.gl/ixcN9) and past the full output of the command.  Also, tail /var/log/dpkg.log and see if anything interesting is there.
http://paste.ubuntu.com/588329/

Looks like dependency problems.  openvpn can't be installed because it requires some other packages.  You'll have to grab liblz02, libpkcs11-helper, openvpn-blacklist and whatever others are needed (probably from the same place as you got the openvpn deb).
Is there some reason you can't use the openvpn packages in the official repository (apt-get install openvpn)?
but there is no other file like that there

Wherever "there" is, why use it instead of the ubuntu repository?  Installing 3rd party .debs is much harder and potentially dangerous compared to using your distro's packages.  There must be a reason you're using other ones.
my ubuntu is offline, I cant go online without fixing up two package, that package will help me to go online
I see.  It'll be tedious, but you'll need to grab all those packages openvpn requires.  I recommend getting them from here: http://packages.ubuntu.com/ for whatever version you're using.
To get a full list of dependencies: "% apt-cache depends openvpn"
can this package openvpn-blacklist_0.1-0ubuntu0.8.04.1_all.deb work for Ubuntu 10.04
No idea.  Seems like you should be able to find an official one for your version though.
cnt find any for 10.04
http://packages.ubuntu.com/lucid/net/ -- Search for openvpn
